cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GT, cs.SI, cs.CV 

This paper involves using machine learning algorithms to analyze game logs and visualize player strategies in a card game. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the following sub-categories: 

- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): This sub-category covers research on machine learning, which is used in this paper to encode game logs and cluster player strategies. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): This sub-category is closely related to cs.AI and covers research on various machine learning algorithms. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory): This sub-category covers research on game theory and its applications in computer science, which is relevant to this paper as it involves analyzing player strategies in a game. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): This sub-category covers research on social networks and their analysis, which is relevant to this paper as it involves analyzing player strategies in a multiplayer game. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): This sub-category covers research on computer vision and image analysis, which is relevant to this paper as it involves visualizing player strategies using t-SNE.
